Rating: 4
Delicious spiced (but not overly spiced) flavor and a lovely firm but moist, chewy texture. I have used the following substitutions with great success: 1) a little less than 1/4 cup blackstrap molasses and a pinch extra brown sugar in lieu of light molasses 2) 1/2 cup butter and 1/4 cup vegetable oil in lieu of 1/2 cup shortening and 1/4 cup butter

Rating: 4
Everything a soft ginger cookie should be! Pure autumnal coziness... I had to double the batch as I found the first batch WAY too salty (and I like my salt). 10 grinds of black pepper too much, stick to 5 - it adds a nice heat. Chopped ginger was better than done in the food processor as it was nice to have little chunks of ginger for both flavour and texture. Way too much cloves for me too, so I added none when I made the second batch. Topped with chunky turbinado sugar. Yum :)

Rating: 4
I have reviewed these cookies before, and am one that uses butter and not shortening. I cut out some of the fat initially (to 1/2 cup from 3/4 cup) and for years had no problems. Then I moved to a new town and a house with a gas stove and things started going south. When my most recent batch came up way runny I did some research. At my former home I had access to bakers cut ginger. Here, I have been using King Arthur ginger chips, and this was the last of a bag, so there was a lot of extra little pieces and extra sugar. I'm guessing that the extra sugar precipitated the flatness. Looking at other recipes, next time I'm going to cut back on butter (to 12 Tbl) and brown sugar (to 2/3 C) and see if that doesn't get me back to cookies that look like the ones in the picture.

Rating: 4
I just checked back here on the site to review this recipe, because I am noticing the exact same thing with my ginger spice cookies seeming flatter and crisper than they had when I made them so many times before. I too like the puffier, softer ginger cookie and mine used to look exactly like the photo for this recipe. I am waiting to see if there is any input from other bakers to see what is causing this problem

