I made these gluten-free and they were totally amazing. Everyone raved and wanted the recipe. I substituted Pamela's Gluten-Free Baking and Pancake Mix for the flour, and reduced the recipe's salt and baking soda by 50% because they're already in the mix. The cookies come out flat no matter how long I chill the dough, but no one cares. I do pulse the crystalized ginger in the food processor with some of the baking mix. I also reversed the colors, using dark molasses and light brown sugar. Simply grand!

