Rating: 4
I am not a fan off overly sweet cookies, so these spice cookies are definitely my new favorite. Since my boyfriend is allergic to wheat products, I made them using Pamela's Baking and Pancake Mix, which is an excellent, easy to use gluten free mix made of brown and white rice flour, almond meal, and a few other wheat-free ingredients (I use this for all my baking anymore and like it better than wheat flour). Anyway, I followed other reviewers suggestions and cut back the brown sugar a bit, added a pinch of cayenne pepper, about 5 or so turns of fresh ground black pepper, and a full cup of chopped crystalized ginger. I also refrigerate overnight (a must with gluten free cookie dough) and bake for about 11 minutes on ungreased, insulated cookie sheets.

Rating: 4
These are delicious cookies! Shortening wasn't available to me so I used an equal amount of butter +2 tablespoons. I used flaky kosher salt and upped the salt to one teaspoon. Don't overdo the packed brown sugar. I packed way too much, but I suspect the recommended one cup is just perfect. About the baking: After my first batch expanded ridiculously, I baked subsequent batches in muffin tins. 3/4 inch ball in each hole. Perfectly round cookies! The sugar dipping makes them sparkly and great.

