I used salted margarine* in place of unsalted butter and reduced the salt to 1/2 tsp. Instead of the egg, I used Ener-G egg replacer in the amount suggested on the box to replace one egg. The results were absolutely fantastic! If anyone would like to make the recipe vegan for themselves or a vegan friend, or just to make them a little healthier (no cholesterol, less saturated fat, etc), I recommend doing them the way I did. I used Earth Balance "buttery sticks" margarine and Spectrum organic shortening, both of which contain no animal-derived ingredients and are free of hydrogenated oils/trans fats as well. Great recipe!

