Rating: 4
Delicious, but I made some changes to make them more intense and more chewy/tough. I like to tear into cookies and wanted a chewy one that wasn't the classic, fluffy moist cookie. So here is my recipe. 2 c flour, 2 tsp ground ginger, 2tsp baking soda,1 tsp cinnamon, 1 tsp cloves, 1/2 tsp cayenne, 10 turns ground black pepper (1/4 - 1/2 tsp), 1 tsp zested fresh ginger, 3/4 tsp salt, 1/3 c granulated sugar, 2/3 cup dark brown sugar, 3/4 - 1 cup chopped crystalized ginger (se Reed's if you can find it, 1/2 c melted butter and 1 egg. I used this recipe to make gingerbread men. I found that it worked best if I rolled the dough out to 3/8 of oan inch, as the expand a lot. This helped them keep their shape a little better. Still, you must leave more space that you might guess between the cookies to ensure that they dont become deformed.

Rating: 4
