A follow-up review - it's still the best ginger cookie recipe out there. I use only 1/2 cup butter, and no shortening. I found that by making them smaller (3/4" to scant 1") in size and baking for 10 minutes, they look exactly like the picture - though smaller of course. They also retain the great crisp/chewy texture. Naturally the yield is doubled by this method. While that might be better in theory for the waistline, in practice it doesn't hold - you just eat more of the gingery little morsels. A classic to be enjoyed for years!

