I'm a big ginger fan and loved these cookies. I thought they might be too much for the "general public", but I took them to two parties in the last week and have gotten rave reviews! In fact I'm baking a second batch this morning because I've run out of them. Please don't leave out the crystallized ginger as suggested by an earlier reviewer- that is what distinguishes these cookies from the boring grocery store variety ginger snap. Several people commented on the "real" ginger in them. I used 1/2 cup butter and NO shortening and they came out great. I only baked for 10 minutes. They look just like the picture and did not spread out too much (as another earlier reviewer commented). For convenience I made up the batter before I went to bed last night and refrigerated overnight. The dough was much easier to work with. I also only took enough out of fridge for one baking sheet at a time.

Rating: 4
These are the BEST ginger cookies ever!!! My husband suggested I post a wee warning to you all... space these well, as they will melt into one another (as did our first batch)... two inches apart is not too far apart; I only placed 6 cookies on my smaller cookie sheets, with fantastic results... and as another suggested, I swithced the butter and shortening amounts to be ½ cup butter & ¼ cup shortening. Be sure they come out after 12 minutes or they will burn, and carefully take them off the cookie sheet and get them on a cooling rack within the first minute of cooling. They will be very hard to resist even though they will be very hot... and they will be very delicious! A definite keeper!!! YUM!!!

