These are terrific. I also replaced the shortening with butter, and added no additional fat--instead, I added 2-3 T of spicy pear butter for moisture. I've done this twice, and they come out crunchy on the edges, and chewy in the middle. The first time I added maybe 8 grinds of black pepper, and the second time I left it out--much better with the pepper. And both times I've made this I haven't had candied ginger, so I grated in an inch and a half of fresh--yum! Rolling these in Muscovado sugar makes them to die for. So pretty, and the crunch of sugar is a great contrast with the kick.

