YUM!!! Definately a keeper. I followed previous advice and replaced butter for shortening and no additional butter. I used light brown sugar and would keep it this way in the future. I added all of the sugared ginger I had on hand (approx. 1 cup unchopped) and this seemed a good amount in the recipe. Also, next time I would add a tsp of white pepper for an additional punch of spice. I doubled the recipe because I was making it for a party I was catering and the recipe says it makes 30 cookies, which wasn't nearly enough. Since they are so spicey I made them smaller and definately think this is the way to go and looks so much prettier on a plate. They easily made 100 cookies doubled, so I guess I'll have extra's for family and friends (which isn't a bad thing). By the way, I baked my cookies for 10 minutes each and they came out wonderfully cracked, crunchy on the outside, soft on the inside, and looking picture perfect.

