Rating: 3
These cookies are amazing. I've been trying to find a recipe for a ginger spice cookie as good as the ginger cookie that Starbucks carries (the only reason I ever go there) - and these are MUCH better. They are very easy to make too. The only reason I am not rating this 4 forks is because I made changes to the recipe, based on other reviewers and my own lack of ingredients. First off - substituting butter for the shortening is A MUST. I used only 1/2 cup unsalted butter as a replacement for both the shortening and butter in the recipe. A buttery taste still came through in the cookies, and I absolutely refuse to bake with shortening so this is key for me. Secondly, because I didn't have enough crystallized ginger, I used 1/4 cup crystallized ginger, 1 large knob of grated fresh ginger and an additional 1/2 tsp of ground ginger. Thirdly, I baked the cookies for only 10 min instead of 12 min. I would make the exact same changes again, as I think 3/4 cup of candied ginger would be too much. Having said all that, a FANTASTIC recipe, goes well with a rainy November night and a glass of cold milk. But really, I'd take it any time... Happy baking. :)

